Short version, it's really depends on the type of anime. ^.^ <p><b>I am, Sesshoumaru: <br>"Names are not important, because you're already dead."</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/useikenmaru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seikenmaru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/02 2:50:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xs4all.nl/~seifer/PkVegeta.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:What makes a good battle??????</span><hr size=1> Now I know it's this:<br>
