What we wanna see is people getting hit once in a while you know? no pointing fighting if nobody get's hit or anything. The thing with i.e. DBZ is one hit won't do much so it takes longer to finish. But in i.e. Kenshin one hit can cut you guts out making it a short battle but a good one cause you see some good action. Some good hits. <br>
<br>
That god enough ^.^ <p><b>I am, Sesshoumaru: <br>"Names are not important, because you're already dead."</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=neoangel>NeoAngel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/02 10:11:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Fighting styles...</span><hr size=1> I like to see different fighting styles. If you've got a zippy but weak guy and a slow but strong guy, it could be good. Think of the ninja philosophy about the elements: I only know a couple of them but they're good. Metal drives with all force into the opponent and never lets up. Not very defensive, more 'the best form of defence is attack' theory. Water flows with and around all attacks (try kicking some and see what I mean). It's very defensive, and allows the opponent to tire out while you retain a lot of your energy so you can then switch to a different 'elemental posture' such as fire (Very aggressive) or metal.<br>
Try to include this in a battle if you've got martial artists.<br>
A street fight tends to be short but brutal, with loads of improvised weapons and blood all over the place.<br>
It really depends on what kinda fight you're trying to draw. But a street fight tends to be fast whereas two skilled martial artists might take a lot longer... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba>The Mamba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/02 12:12:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=64>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fighting styles...</span><hr size=1> Short fights can be some of the best fights ever. Some great examples of really good short fights can be found throughout the whole Cowboy Bebop series. Most of the fights in that never lasted more than 2 minutes and they all kicked ass. <br>
<br>
NeoAngel, what you said about the big slow guy and the little zippy guy is so very true. Just think how cool a fight between Spiderman and Juggernaut would be (they've probably already had a fight or two but I haven't bought a comic book in soooooooooooo long <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p>I am the Insular Dotard<br>
