But if by chance I turn vicious<br>
I'll chew on your head like a fig.<br><br>

<a href="http://InsularDotard.freeservers.com">The Insular Dotard</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanimelibra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>animelibra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/30/02 8:53:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=65>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fighting styles...</span><hr size=1> I agree with neoangel too. It's also really funny when you watch some slow guy just get the crap beaten out of him because he doesn't know where to hit.<br>
<br>
NO CORNEY PHRASES!!!!!! If you want to see some examples, watch the oringinal live-action Batman. *shudders* biff, wham, everywhere....can it with the bad puns Robin....<br>
<br>
I love the fights in Cowboy Bebop. Part of a really great battle is just how you draw the characters and the weapons if any. Also, vengence is sweet. And if your gonna have people punching each other, gloves would be cool; you gotta protect your hand somehow, huh?<br>
<br>
Different points of veiw are good in moderation. Instead of the plain ol' side shot of a guy/girl shooting someone why not see it through the person getting shot? (I mean right BEFORE the blood goes spewing)<br>
<br>
Keep the flashbacks to a minimum unless you just want to torture the audience. And a good enterence (sp?) is good. I think it's pretty cool when someone comes in 30 above the air on a motorcycle and lands to fight. (or even better, lands on the person! ::roll ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=angelziome>Angel Ziome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/9/02 1:58:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1526.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Fighting styles...</span><hr size=1> Personally, I dont think you can compare DBZ fights to basically ANY other Anime. DBZ is just to differen't. Not that thats a bad thing, but it's just not everyone's cup of tea. Personally I love seeing loooong battles, it gets really exciting, seeing people fight with so much Energy and power. Knowing that if in an equal fight, there are almost never one hit kills so all the fights turn out awsome. Really though, another thing about Ki energy, is that it too is something that you have to have a taste for. I love it, the way they fight with energy. All I have to say is, Akira must have a very interesting mind to think up the DB series...some verrrryy unique stuff. No matter how much some people hate it, you have got admit that it is pretty damn unique.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#336699>- </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs>Polykarbon BBS</a><font color=#336699> - </font><a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4>General Manga/Anime Discussion</a> <font color=#336699> - </font><a href="http://www.polykarbon.com">Polykarbon